FancyString
===========

If you want to use SEO url, use this little plugin. Fancy_string extends standard String class. Anywhere you can call "bla blah".fancy method

SEO url is better than "/articles/1". You can simple get url like "/articles/1/my-first-article"


Example
=======

"My COOL fancy string".fancy
# => "my-cool-fancy-string"


Real example
============

Imagine, we have a articles controller.

1. Add this route, to allow additional parameter *fancy
   
    map.article 'article/:id/*fancy', :controller => 'article', :action => 'show'

2. Then use link_to helper like this:

    # Controller
    @article = Article.find(params[:id])

    # View
    <%= link_to @article.title, article_path(@article, @article.title.fancy)

    # output

    <a href="/article/1/my-first-article">My first article</a>


